$interpreted: Jahan: What a morning... Thankfully my sweet-talking worked. We didn't have to deal with a furious King.
Dylan: What did you tell his Majesty?
Jahan: Find out the name of its master before you kick the dog. After all, that little girl is indeed a daughter of the Aldric family.
Jahan: His Majesty likely does not want things to get messy with the Twelve Nobles.
Dylan: That girl...her name is Sione, right?
Jahan: Tsk. Don't know what's wrong with her. What kind of idiot leaves behind a fancy noble lifestyle to enlist in the army?
Jahan: Oh, speak of the devil. Must be here to patrol the venue. What? Dylan got a thing for her?
Dylan: ......
Rookie Soldier: Whew... nothing unusual.
Sione: Seems like it. Still, we shouldn't let our guard down.
Rookie Soldier: Y-Yes. Pardon me, Lady Aldric!
Sione: ...I am indeed of the Aldric family. But now I'm just a soldier, like you. So, I would appreciate it if you just called me Sione.
Rookie Soldier: ...Th-Then, Miss Sione...
Sione: Just Sione, please.
Rookie Soldier: Then, Sione... you are one of the Twelve Nobles. Why did you leave behind a life of luxury to pursue a career in the army?
Sione: ...Being a noble has its merits, but it comes with many restraints. Take today's engagement party for example.
Rookie Soldier: From what I've heard, this marriage was organized by King Theodore himself.
Sione: Yes. My older sisters had to go through political marriages just like this one.
Sione: I don't want to suffer the same fate...
Sione: Beasts? Why are they here?
Rookie Soldier: Are these the ones King Theodore brought in this morning...
Sione: These beasts should be in cages! Who let them out!?
Male Guest: Ahhhhhhhh! Help! Help!
Sione: No!
Sione: Everything is settled now.
Male Noble: Royal Infantry! Where is the Royal Infantry?
Sione: ...Aren't you the groom? What happened?
Male Noble: My fiancée is missing!
Sione: What?
Male Noble: You guys are the Royal Infantry, right? Help me find her!
Sione: ...False alarm?? Damn, we were tricked!!
Rookie Soldier: Eh? W-Wait for me. Sione!
